reviews.text: A really expensive cafe and food quality is just average. Children are happy because of the tablewares and meal presentation. For parents, there is a place for relaxing. Service is just ok, compared with few years ago, a kid flip his pudding upside down, the waitress got a new one for him without additional charge. It was really impressive.
There are also pasta, lasagna and katsudon. The  meal menu is roughly around 2000 yen. I did not see it in the menu, but there was something like afternoon tea.
Afternoon tea set is average, reasonable and not totally unexpected for theme park dining. Nice place to rest your feet and people watch. Not necessarily the best place to view the parade
Aattractive family restaurant offering good window view of passersby. Cocacola and colorful smooth drinks available. Seafood pasta very nice.

Got a table for five 15 minutes before the fireworks and the waiters and waitresses told us if we wanted to keep our table while we watched the fireworks, they'd gladly do that for us. All that to say, they're thoughtful and provide superb services. The food wasn't amazing, but it was decent for amusement park standard. It's quite pricey as well, which was expected.

reviews.text: Disneyland Hong Kong is a very big theme park with rides, shows, music, parade, fireworks, animated people, etc, etc. Always crowed with people enjoying wearing Micky headband. The adventure land shows are exquisite. Almost all shows are perfectly performed and the lighting is fantastic. The Tarzan tree house is almost real. Can easily reach by Hong Kong Metro.

A bit crowded at times but the rides are high quality and the shows are all well made. I'd prefer if they set up more fast pass ques, or sold them, as the ques on anything but a normal weekday can be daunting.
Hong Kong Disneyland is a great and fun place to visit. Kids and adults will enjoy themselves thoroughly. The staff are friendly and always willing to help. Highly recommended 👍

Had a very fun rainy day here. Less people and basically no line up for any ride. Very different Disneyland experience that I'm used to. Usually the day is spent for lining up for attractions but this is probably the least visited Disneyland. Loved it.
Enjoyable, but think they need to set up more fans during the warmer months. A bit too many people for a truly enjoyable experience. F&B are pricey, but expected for amusement parks.
香港其中一個旅遊熱點👍🏻
可以在一天玩爽玩好的迪士尼樂園❤️😍❤️
去過東京的就覺的香港的還好😅
氣氛及環境不錯👍🏻
好喜愛童話地方😀😀😀

reviews.text:
最初はあまりパーク内のレストランの食事の味は期待していなかったのですが、
パスタもサラダも味付けがよくて美味しかったです～！！

見た目もニンジンがミッキーの形になっていたり、
ドリンクの上にシェリーメイとクッキーが乗っていてかわいかったです(^^)/

ボリュームが多いので、２人でシェアしてこの料でちょうどよかったです！

女性だけで食べるなら、サラダ、メインなど１品ずつ頼んでシェアするのをオススメします♪

ドリンクもなかなかボリュームありました☆

他にも、トムヤムクンを味見したのですが、酸味がきいてて美味しかったです(*^▽^*)

在樂園中價錢比其他餐廳貴一點，但食物水準真的很差，不是要求什麼佳餚美食，但真的比起很多茶餐廳都不如。

服務員態度ok, 但不專業，令人有點失望。
雞肉好硬。又貴又不特別
ハンバーガーゼットで170HKD。日本円だと約2400円くらい。日本人の自分からしたら少し高いです。味はまあ良し、ボリュームはかなりありました。女子なら2人で1セットでも良いくらいの量。

A really expensive cafe and food quality is just average. Children are happy because of the tablewares and meal presentation. For parents, there is a place for relaxing. Service is just ok, compared with few years ago, a kid flip his pudding upside down, the waitress got a new one for him without additional charge. It was really impressive.
